    "body": "Here I list a serie of possible removals for make the nupic repo clearer and easy to follow and maintain as discussed in ML. Some of these removals should also be aplied to nupic.core in case of equivalent code (numenta/nupic.core#354).\r\n\r\n* * *\r\n\r\n`nupic/research`:\r\n- [X] Dead code (`DataGenerator.py`, `ObjDiff.py`, `TrainingHooks.py`, `TrainingHooks.py`, `anomalyzer.py`). These dead codes are used in anywhere (except in their tests/examples). Issue: https://github.com/numenta/nupic/issues/1857, Fixed by: https://github.com/numenta/nupic/pull/1858\r\n- [X] Derived implementations of SP (`flat_spatial_pooler.py`): This removal already was discussed. Issue: https://github.com/numenta/nupic/issues/627, Fixed by: https://github.com/numenta/nupic/pull/1851\r\n- [X] Obsolete implementations of SP (`FDRCSpatial2.py` and `fdrutilities.py`): Do we really need this old implementation as `spatial_pooler` is its replacement?. Another point, `fdrutilities.py` has a lot of dead code. By the way, if`FDRCSpatial2.py` be removed then this file also could be removed. Issue: https://github.com/numenta/nupic/issues/1864\r\n- [X] Derived implementations of TP (`TPTrivial.py` and `TrivialPredictor.py`): I've checked the use of these classes in code, and I found that are little used. Issue: https://github.com/numenta/nupic/issues/1865\r\n- [ ] Obsolete implementations of TP (`TP.py`, `TP10X2.py`, and their crutchs: `TP_shim.py` and `TemporalMemoryShim.py`): When `temporal_memory` gets more mature, could `TP.py` and `TP10X2.py` be removed? If so, then `TP_shim.py` and `TemporalMemoryShim.py` will not make more sense.\r\n- [ ] Derived implementations of TM (`fast_temporal_memory.py`): Is this derived class very important?\r\n- [X] Vision code; In #1863 \r\n\r\nIt seems that TP is the big problem to a clean repository as it has several derived classes and hacks to keep consistency between them. As `temporal_memory` gets mature, we could remove TP and its inheritance and so the repository finally would get nice and clean. By the way, while TP is not fully removed, some derived classes could be removed right now (`TPTrivial`, `fast_temporal_memory`, etc).",
    "repo": "numenta/nupic"
