    "body": "edit:\r\nwe discussed this with @chetan51 back then, I will try to investigate this issue again - if it is possible to extract Boosting/Inhibition functionality from SP/TP to stand-alone classes. \r\npros:\r\n* simpler SP/TP/(TM?) code\r\n* code shared among implementations\r\n* code shared among different classes SP/TP,...\r\n\r\ncons:\r\n* there are (easy) optimizations for some cases -- with right data-structure, we can optimize (using eg GPU lib) for all cases\r\n\r\n\r\n----------------------\r\nI think we should (again) create a class `Boosting` (or BoostingStrategy ?) that would take care of the logic of: \r\nwhen should it start boosting? \r\nwhich columns? \r\nand how \"strongly\" to boost? \r\n\r\nThen we could easily have implementations: GreedyBoosting (now), SmoothBoosting, PartialBoosting (1 at a time)...",
