    "closed_at": null,
    "body": "There are a bunch of odd things with the build that need to be fixed.\r\n\r\n- The `.i` and generated `.cxx` files get installed in regular non-develop builds which should be avoided\r\n- The <repo>/build directory is created (even when a different install location is specified) and some build artifacts are copied there. But it doesn't seem to serve any purpose. We should remove it as we don't want any arbitrary hard-coded locations in our setup.py file. And it shouldn't be necessary since setuptools should automatically create a temp dir for intermediate steps\r\n- The `.capnp` files are not included in the specified installation location. They are getting moved to the hard-coded `build/...` location\r\n- Build artifacts like the `.so` files are copied into the source tree as well as the installation location. They should only be copied to the installation location (or the repo location if it is a developer build?)\r\n- In develop mode, a nupic.egg-link file specifies the repo location. In this case, all generated files or files from nupic.core must be copied to the repo location or additionally need to be included in the `.egg-link` file.\r\n\r\nRelates to #1670 \r\nCC @rhyolight @oxtopus @david-ragazzi ",
    "repo": "numenta/nupic"
