    "body": "As described by @subutai [here](https://github.com/numenta/nupic/issues/724#issuecomment-38321427):\r\n\r\n> With one exception, all the code under the old `nta` directory is pure C++ and should be available within `nupic.core`. Many of the libraries (such as math libraries) are also made available to Python through bindings but they are not specific to Python and not dependent on Python.\r\n>\r\n> The one exception is the following. The NuPIC Network API includes the concept of Regions. Regions are the main extensible building blocks. C++ Regions can be written, like VectorFileSensor. But, we also allow Python Regions to be written. `nta/engine/RegionImplFactory.cpp` includes a class called `DynamicPythonLibrary` that contains code to dynamically load Python code and treat that as if it is a Region.  This is the one piece of Python logic that is still in `nupic.core`. It doesn’t seem to actually import any Python include files so perhaps it’s not too bad. Removing this bit might taksome work - we probably need to move that functionality to a shared library and move it out of `nupic.core`.  We do need to keep the basic functionality though - we use a lot of Python regions.\r\n>\r\n> The bindings code for the C++ API is mostly in `lang` and IMHO should not be in `nupic.core`.  This includes `libsupport` which I think is mostly to help translate between the core C++ and the Python `numpy` module.  None of this code needs to be in `nupic.core`.\r\n>\r\n> `py` directory is all Python related code. Included in here is `py/bindings` which is for binding to Regions and also other C++ libraries.  `py/regions` include the Python Regions such as CLARegion.py. `py/nupic` is the main NuPIC python code and contains a lot of stuff. None of this should be in `nupic.core`.\r\n>\r\n> I think all the tests except for `htmtest` and `testeverything` are Python driven tests and shouldn’t be in `nupic.coe`.\r\n\r\n`nupic.core` depends on `cpp_region` in `nupic` which in turn loads Python implementations of regions.\r\n\r\nIn this dependency, there're environment variable `$NTA` and library name `libcpp_region`.\r\n\r\nThis dependency is circular and not general, so it's not good for `nupic.core` to become a stand-alone library.\r\n\r\nNot proposing any actions yet, just log an issue here for future follow up.\r\n\r\nB.T.W. @subutai 's description on this issue is an excellent source for wiki write-up regarding this dependency, thus I would like to quote here:\r\n\r\n> The NuPIC Network API includes the concept of Regions. Regions are the main extensible building blocks. C++ Regions can be written, like VectorFileSensor. But, we also allow Python Regions to be written. nta/engine/RegionImplFactory.cpp includes a class called DynamicPythonLibrary that contains code to dynamically load Python code and treat that as if it is a Region. This is the one piece of Python logic that is still in nupic.core. It doesn’t seem to actually import any Python include files so perhaps it’s not too bad. Removing this bit might take some work - we probably need to move that functionality to a shared library and move it out of nupic.core. We do need to keep the basic functionality though - we use a lot of Python regions.\r\n",
    "repo": "numenta/nupic.core"
